		<body>
		  <p rend="align(right)"><date>1844</date>.</p>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Alpen</placeName>&#44; <date>Friday</date>&#44; pericope Vaylkran&#44; &#40;Maron[&#63;]&#41;<lb/></p>
			<p>May there be great peace&#44; mercy and kindness to my nephew&#44; the wise<lb/> <persName>Isaac</persName>&#44; etc.&#44;</p>
		  <p rend="indent(1)">I have one more request to make of you&#44; namely that I still<lb/> look forward to your sending me that which you have promised me more than<lb/> two whole years ago.  Even though it is across the sea&#44; do not say&#44; &#34;Who<lb/> will cross it for us&#63;&#34;.  Only let the road be near in your heart to do it.&#42;<lb/>  Believe me&#44; upon my word of honor&#44; that if I did not find myself <sic>ina</sic> bad<lb/> position&#44; I would not send you this any more at the present time&#44; at least not<lb/> put in such a tone&#44; since my letter of a year ago&#44; in the spring&#44; has re&#45;<lb/>mained unnoticed and unanswered.  I have not been compensated with a few lines even<lb/> for my postage expense.  Even if my request remained unfulfilled&#44; it<lb/> would still have been very pleasant to have been able to say that I had<lb/> received a letter from my relative in <placeName>America</placeName>.  But this&#44; too&#44; was not<lb/> granted me.  Well&#44; then&#44; dear <persName>Itzik</persName>&#44; if you want to fulfill your promise&#44;<lb/> do it now or not at all&#44; and show that you still have some regard for<lb/> your old uncle.  My position is already known to you from my previous<lb/> letter.  It has become worse rather than better.  What is more&#44; I find<lb/> it quite unnecessary to expose to you my entire present situation.  You<lb/> know it well enough if you want <sic>tohelp</sic>.</p>
		  <p rend="indent(1)">Recently&#44; I read about you in the &#34;Zeitung des Judentums&#34;&#44;<lb/> by <persName>Dr. Philippson</persName>&#44; that you are [&#63;]uiting a monthly.  This proves that you<lb/> are in correspondence with <placeName>Europe</placeName>.  You can therefore direct a few lines<lb/> to me&#44; even though you may not be able or willing to help me.  My family<lb/> in <placeName>DÃ¼lmen</placeName>&#44; <placeName>Rheine</placeName>&#44; and <placeName>Barmen</placeName> are all&#44; thank God&#44; in good health.  I hope<lb/> to hear the same from you as soon as possible.  That is my most fervent<lb/> wish.</p>
		  <p rend="indent(1)">With wishes for your life&#44; and peace&#44; and length of days<lb/> and years&#44; from the ever&#45;living God&#44; I remain as ever&#44;</p>
		  <p rend="indent(2)">Your uncle <persName role="author">Abraham</persName>&#44; son of</p>
		  <p rend="indent(3)"><persName>Eliesar Leeser</persName></p>
			<p>&#42; Up to this point in Hebrew&#44; based on Deuteronomy 30&#58;12&#45;13.</p>
